.TH "of_hwspin_lock_simple_xlate" 9 "of_hwspin_lock_simple_xlate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_hwspin_lock_simple_xlate \- translate hwlock_spec to return a lock id
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_hwspin_lock_simple_xlate
.BI "(const struct of_phandle_args *hwlock_spec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hwlock_spec" 12
hwlock specifier as found in the device tree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a simple translation function, suitable for hwspinlock platform
drivers that only has a lock specifier length of 1.

Returns a relative index of the lock within a specified bank on success,
or -EINVAL on invalid specifier cell count.
